about.summary: An alternative approach to non-standard evaluation using formulas. Provides a full implementation of LISP style 'quasiquotation', making it easier to generate code with other code.

name: r-lazyeval
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.2.2' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-lazyeval
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/lazyeval_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/lazyeval/lazyeval_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d6904112a21056222cfcd5eb8175a78aa063afe648a562d9c42c6b960a8820d4

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 2
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('lazyeval')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('lazyeval')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=lazyeval
  license: GPL-3
  summary: An alternative approach to non-standard evaluation using formulas. Provides a full
    implementation of LISP style 'quasiquotation', making it easier to generate code
    with other code.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
